On Oct 22, 2007, at 1:18 PM, DurocShark wrote:

> There should never be one downstream of the fuel pump,
> regardless of what you see done to bugs.

I fixed a '72 bus that had 3 filters (one between tank and pump, one  
before each float bowl). It was neat to be able to see the fuel  
present but the engine always had trouble starting with the extra  
filters (trapped air I guess).

